$font[serif,20]{Alchemy Window help}\n$font[serif,16]{0. General info}\nYou can drop ingredients with known effects and exixirs with known recipes onto this window to record them:\n• ingredients will store their effects and can be viewed in $b{Ingredients} tab\n• elixirs will record their effect and recipe in $b{Recipes} tab\n• all "natural" (non-processed) ingredients from exlixir will be marked in $b{Combos} tab as tested against each other\n\nIf "Limit recipe storing" checkbox is on, then elixir recipes will be saved only if  $b{Recipes} tab is open.\n\n\n$font[serif,16]{1. Ingredients tab}\nShows list of known ingredients with their effects. List can be filtered by name or by effects. \n$col[246,229,34]{TODO: add filter details!}\n\n$font[serif,16]{2. Recipes tab}\nShows list of recorder elixir recipes. Selected recipe can be renamed, can be removed or you can open recipe on the Yoda's Alchemy Graph site.\nElixirs can be filtered by name, effects and ingredients.\n$col[246,229,34]{TODO: add filter details!}\n\n$font[serif,16]{3. Combos tab}\nShows list of all known ingredients and for each such ingredient shows against which other ingredients it was tested.\nTabs over second list can show all, already tested and not-tested ingredients.\nHighlight checkbox will open small window and start highlighting all ingredients that are not yet tested against selected one. You can drop elixirs and ingredients on this small window for same effect as dropping them on the main Alchemy Window.\nNote: not all ingredients are in this list by default - only those I knew about and had resource names for. But if you drop unknown ingredient or elixir with one - it will be added to this ingredient list automatically.